{"max_tokens":8192,"messages":[{"content":"You are a senior SystemVerilog verification engineer. Given the structured test plan, generate a complete SystemVerilog testbench. Include a clock generator, reset logic, basic scoreboard, and assertions. Output ONLY the raw SystemVerilog code without markdown formatting (no ```sv ... ```).","role":"system"},{"content":"{\n  \"module_name\": \"systolic_array\",\n  \"inputs\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"clk\",\n      \"width\": \"1-bit\",\n      \"description\": \"Positive edge clock signal\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"rst_n\",\n      \"width\": \"1-bit\",\n      \"description\": \"Negative edge reset\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"valid_in\",\n      \"width\": \"1-bit\",\n      \"description\": \"Valid signal set to 1 when a valid data are settled on 'matrix_a_in' and 'matrix_b_in' so the DUT is allowed to sample them\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"matrix_a_in\",\n      \"width\": \"N_SIZE*DATAWIDTH\",\n      \"description\": \"Array of N inputs corresponding to one column of matrix A elements entering the systolic array rows.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"matrix_b_in\",\n      \"width\": \"N_SIZE*DATAWIDTH\",\n      \"description\": \"Array of N inputs corresponding to one row of matrix B elements entering the systolic array columns.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outputs\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"valid_out\",\n      \"width\": \"1-bit\",\n      \"description\": \"Valid signal set to 1 when a valid row of the result matrix are settled on 'matrix_c_out'\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"matrix_c_out\",\n      \"width\": \"N_SIZE*2*DATAWIDTH\",\n      \"description\": \"Array of 5 outputs corresponding to one row of matrix C elements resulting from the array multiplication\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"tests\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"reset_test\",\n      \"type\": \"functional\",\n      \"description\": \"Verify the synchronous negative edge reset functionality. Ensure all internal registers and outputs are initialized to their default states after a reset assertion.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"single_valid_input_propagation\",\n      \"type\": \"functional\",\n      \"description\": \"Apply a single set of valid 'matrix_a_in' and 'matrix_b_in' with 'valid_in' asserted for one clock cycle. Observe the propagation delay and verify 'valid_out' asserts and 'matrix_c_out' shows the correct result after the expected latency.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"continuous_valid_inputs\",\n      \"type\": \"functional\",\n      \"description\": \"Apply a stream of valid 'matrix_a_in' and 'matrix_b_in' continuously with 'valid_in' always asserted. Verify that 'valid_out' remains asserted and 'matrix_c_out' continuously outputs correct results for sequential matrix multiplications.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"staggered_valid_inputs\",\n      \"type\": \"functional\",\n      \"description\": \"Apply 'valid_in' at irregular intervals (e.g., 'valid_in' asserted for 1 cycle, then deasserted for several, then asserted again). Ensure the DUT correctly processes the data when 'valid_in' is high and holds previous data when 'valid_in' is low, without corruption.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"multiplication_zero_matrices\",\n      \"type\": \"functional\",\n      \"description\": \"Provide 'matrix_a_in' and 'matrix_b_in' where all elements are zero. Verify that 'matrix_c_out' also produces all zeros, reflecting the correct multiplication outcome.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"multiplication_identity_matrix\",\n      \"type\": \"functional\",\n      \"description\": \"Provide 'matrix_a_in' as an identity matrix (if applicable to the input format) and a known 'matrix_b_in'. Verify that 'matrix_c_out' matches 'matrix_b_in' (or the product as expected).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"multiplication_various_data\",\n      \"type\": \"functional\",\n      \"description\": \"Test with various data patterns for 'matrix_a_in' and 'matrix_b_in', including positive, negative (if DATAWIDTH is signed), and mixed values. Compare 'matrix_c_out' against a golden reference model.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"edge_case_max_value_data\",\n      \"type\": \"functional\",\n      \"description\": \"Test with 'matrix_a_in' and 'matrix_b_in' containing maximum possible values for the given DATAWIDTH. Check for correct multiplication and accumulation without overflow (if overflows are handled), or verify expected overflow behavior.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"random_data_test\",\n      \"type\": \"random\",\n      \"description\": \"Generate random 'matrix_a_in' and 'matrix_b_in' values along with random 'valid_in' patterns. Verify resulting 'matrix_c_out' against a software reference model over a large number of cycles.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"parameterized_datawidth_variation\",\n      \"type\": \"parameterized\",\n      \"description\": \"Vary DATAWIDTH parameter for different simulation runs (e.g., DATAWIDTH=8, DATAWIDTH=32) and repeat a subset of functional tests to ensure scalability and correctness across different data widths.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"parameterized_n_size_variation\",\n      \"type\": \"parameterized\",\n      \"description\": \"Vary N_SIZE parameter for different simulation runs (e.g., N_SIZE=2, N_SIZE=4) and repeat a subset of functional tests to confirm the systolic array scales correctly with different matrix dimensions.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"concurrent_reset_during_operation\",\n      \"type\": \"functional\",\n      \"description\": \"Assert 'rst_n' during an ongoing matrix multiplication sequence. Verify that the DUT immediately resets and 'valid_out' deasserts, and next valid operation starts cleanly from initial state.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"read_after_valid_out_deassertion\",\n      \"type\": \"functional\",\n      \"description\": \"After 'valid_out' deasserts, ensure that 'matrix_c_out' maintains its last valid output for a reasonable period or goes to a defined default value, rather than showing garbage data.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"data_flow_verification_4th_clk_edge\",\n      \"type\": \"functional\",\n      \"description\": \"Specifically verify the input data loading as depicted in the '4th Clk edge' diagram, ensuring 'valid_in=0' correctly prevents sampling of 'matrix_a_in' and 'matrix_b_in' and output remains stable.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"data_flow_verification_1st_row_output\",\n      \"type\": \"functional\",\n      \"description\": \"Validate the correct output sequence for 'matrix_c_out' as corresponding to the '1st row of output matrix' diagram (C11, C12, C13), ensuring data emerges in the correct order and timing.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}","role":"user"}],"model":"codestral-latest","response_format":{"type":"json_object"}}
